                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 714.1515/9</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Leavell</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-20T17:00:00-06:02">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 20, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to Minister Ewing’s cablegram of February nineteenth to the Department
                    and repeated to me. I am informed that the Cuyamel Fruit Company had an agent in
                    Guatemala recently trying to secure a concession in this very same disputed
                    territory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leavell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
